HEADWORD: Corallorhiza
<hw>Corallorhiza</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a genus of leafless
root-parasitic orchids having small purplish or yellowish racemose
flowers with lobed lips; it is widely distributed in temperate
regions.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Corallorhiza</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

